AS AT THE founding of the People’s Republic, the 70th anniversary of Communist rule in China featured a tightly controlled parade bristling with the country’s latest military kit. That marks a sharp contrast to the growing chaos in Hong Kong, where a protest spirit has sparked new art and an impromptu anthem. And we ask if hot-desking costs employees more than companies are saving. Runtime: 20 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn